    tern:instructions """
    <h3 id="instructions-and-procedures">Instructions and procedures</h3>
<ol type="1">
  <li>
    <p>
      Ensure the <em>Plot selection and layout</em> module has been completed to
      mark out the plot grid with sub-metre accuracy using the Trimble® R1.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Select the ‘Soils’ module and then the ‘Soil pit characterisation’
      protocol in the App. The App will automatically record the Plot name,
      based on the established plot you are working in, the Protocol, and the
      Date.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Locate the southwest corner of the plot.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Record the <em>Type of soil observation</em> being used (drop-down list).
      This should be ‘P’ (Soil pit) for pedologists or experience soil surveyors
      (continue with
      <u
        ><a href="#soil-pit-characterisation-and-soil-sample-collection"
          >Soil pit characterisation and soil sample</a
        ></u
      >
      <u>collection</u> below), or ‘T’ (10 cm samples) extracted via ‘P’ (Soil
      pit) for less experienced field surveyors (skip to
      <a href="#soil-sub-site-samples-protocol"><u>Soil sample</u></a>
      <u>collection</u>). Refer to pages 205–206 of the YB for further
      descriptions.
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>
<h4 id="soil-pit-characterisation-and-soil-sample-collection">
  A. Soil pit characterisation and soil sample collection
</h4>
<ol start="5" type="1">
  <li>
    <p>
      Record who the soil pit characterisation is
      <em>Characterised by</em> from the drop-down list of personnel affiliated
      with your user login.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Dig a soil pit to 1 m+ deep just outside the southwest corner of the plot.
      Place the spoil on a ground sheet to minimise disturbance and assist
      backfilling. Record the <em>Depth</em> of the soil pit.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      If a depth of 1 m+ cannot be achieved after three attempts, record what
      digging was <em>Stopped by</em> (drop-down list) and the
      <em>R horizon depth</em> in metres.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Assess which face of the pit is best for photographing, taking into
      consideration angle of the sun and shadows. Position the pit tape on the
      left or right edge of the best face and select the 'Soil pit photo' button
      to capture an image using your device's camera.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Identify the soil horizons in the soil profile. Select the ‘Add soil
      horizon’ button to record soil profile data for the first soil horizon.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>
      Record the <em>Horizon</em> and <em>Horizon suffix</em> using the codes
      from the drop-down list. Refer to pages 148–159 of the YB and the
      <a href="#additional-guidelines"><u>Additional guidelines</u></a>
